12:
Looks like wielding your new Alter
Device is second nature to you at
this point.
17:
I heard you let Love and Renoir do
some diagnostics on you. Find
anything interesting?
21:
It appears that I am classified as an
"organic." Therefore, I am something
close to human. However, they
believe my powers were created
artificially.
23:
I was... incredibly surprised at the
results.
27:
I'm just glad you're all right. We've all
been worried about you since you
recovered that core.
47:
You dance with such beauty and
grace.
51:
Heehee, glad you enjoyed the show!
Why don't you give it a try, too?
55:
Me, dance? I am afraid I was not
programmed to perform such a
function...
59:
...But, perhaps I could learn if you are
willing to teach me.
62:
Actually, there is something
weighing heavily on my mind. Could
you spare a moment to listen?
68:
So he told you to butt out, huh?
Haridal never was one to mince
words...
72:
Yes. But I cannot simply abandon
the borderlands.
75:
And yet... I remain troubled by this
decision.
77:
What Haridal said is true. Power of
this caliber has the potential to
sway and corrupt.
88:
I have a sense that, as long as I am
with all of you... everything will be all
right.
96:
This is... illogical. Perhaps it is
irresponsible of me to say this, but...
98:
My belief in the people here far
outweighs my doubt.
101: I know... that I can trust you all.
103:
You all taught me that power does
not always beget violence.
105:
Maybe I, too, can convince Haridal
of the same.
108:
Because I believe in this place. In
you, Stella, and everyone in Starview
Village.
110:
Just as Rashid believed in me. And
just as I believed in him...
119:
I... I am beginning to feel an
overwhelming sense of
embarrassment. P-please say
something!
124:
...You've really become quite the
charmer, Sotieth. You seductive little
minx!
134:
Ahaha! I kid, I kid—I couldn't help it!
The sincerity of your words was just
so moving.
137:
You must've been dying to tell
someone. But... why share all of this
with me?
141:
Your insight is very important to me.
Back then, it was you who helped
me recognize my... my love for
Rashid.
145:
C'mon, you're definitely flirting with
me at this point.
150:
N-no! I have no such lecherous
intentions!
154:
I just... know that I can always count
on you. Speaking of which...
157:
Are you still willing to teach me how
to dance?
161:
Pfft... Ahahaha! After all of that, I
almost forgot!
164: Of course. Let's shake it, Sotieth!
175:
All troops, halt! From here on out,
we'll be in enemy territory. Be ready
for—
179:
There will be no need for battle. We
have already subdued the bandits.
184: ...You sure you don't need any help?
193:
I thought I made myself clear, last
we talked.
197: I refuse to abandon the borderlands.
206: I see there's no changing your mind.
212:
Destroying the kingdom or
abandoning this power are not our
only options.
214:
I have learned there are always
other ways forward, from the many
allies I have been blessed with.
217:
And... I refuse to let my love for
Rashid and his dream lose to yours.
225:
That is why I have come to you with
a proposal.
233:
I aim to establish an alliance with
the borderlands and negotiate with
the kingdom. Will you join us?
238:
Rakisha and her pals've been hard
at work laying the groundwork for
the alliance. It's not impossible.
242:
We need all of the help we can
muster. Our alliance would not be
complete without you.
244:
However, the choice is yours. I do
not wish to force you.
249:
I'm not promising anything... but I'll
hear you out. Then we'll go from
there.
254:
Of course. Let us build this land
anew. Together.
